 Tshirt, jeans and blazer Photo ChiomaGoodHair “Don’t be into trends. Don’t make fashion own you, but decide what you are, what you want to express by the way you dress and the way you live.” – Gianni Versace Wearing trendy clothes with the latest hairstyle, clothing, and lifestyle has been known to be fashion, but fashion in the real sense is a form of self-expression through your clothing, foot wear, life style, accessories, make up, hairstyle and body posture, in other words you do not have to break your budget to look fashionable. Now that we have establish the fact that we do not need to follow trend to be fashionable, lets talk Fashion, on a budget. You could have a killer wardrobe while saving money doing it. Today ill be sharing a few tip that has proven to be a must know when styling on a budget. Toke Makinwa | Instagram Beach Date Outfit Ideas Photo Instagram @thisthingcalledfashionn Being fashionable on a budget doesn’t have to mean skipping out on shopping entirely. These tips will help you build a stylish wardrobe without breaking the bank. The faster you shift your mindset, the more effective your shopping strategy and style will be. Set your trend without breaking the bank.